{{Infobox Institute |name=G. V. Kurdyumov Institute for Metal Physics (IMP) of the National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine (NASU) |image= [[File:KyivInsituteMF.jpg|200px|Main building of the institute]] |caption= Main building of the institute |established= 1945 |staff=600 |address=36 Acad. Vernadsky Boulevard, UA-03142 Kyiv, Ukraine |type=[[Academic Institute]] |city=[[Kiev]] |head_label=Director |head=Orest M. Ivasishin |country=[[Ukraine]] |website=[http://www.imp.kiev.ua/ http://www.imp.kiev.ua/] }}
The '''G. V. Kurdyumov Institute for Metal Physics (IMP) of the [[National Academy of Sciences of Ukraine]]''' ({{lang-uk|Інститут металофізики ім. Г. В. Курдюмова Національної академії наук України}}) is one of the oldest research institutions of physical science within the Academy.
The research institute was established in 1945 as a laboratory of the Black Metallurgy ([[Ferrous metallurgy|Ferrous Metallurgy]]) Institute. In 1955 it was turned into a separate research institute.
Currently, the Institute employs more than 300 researchers (together with several Full Members and Corresponding Members of the NASU) and around 300 peoples of supporting personnel. It has more than 20 scientific units (including the state-of-the-art hardware) which are grouped around several research programs.
Traditionally, the Institute is focused on fundamental research. At the same time, applied research on metals, their [[alloy]]s, and related nanotechnologies strengthen the Institute's activities.
The IMP is consistently ranked at the top of national academic institutions ranking. Besides, international reputation of IOP is growing constantly as prominent scientists from the Institute expand their activity to leading foreign research centers and universities.
==Directors== * 1945 — 1951 [[Georgii Kurdyumov]] * 1951 — 1954 [[Vitaliy Danylov]] * 1955 [[Adrian Smirnov]] * 1955 — 1985 [[Vitaliy Gridnev]] * 1985 — 1989 [[Viktor Bariakhtar]] * 1989 — 2002 [[Volodymyr Nemoshkalenko]] * 2002 — 2011 [[Anatoliy Shpak]] * 2011 — [[Orest Ivasyshyn]]
